CHOLERA, DIARRHEA AND DYSENTERY UPDATE (38): NEPAL
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
[1] Cholera - Nepal (Rautahat District)
[2] Diarrhea - Nepal (Bajura District)
[3] Diarrhea - Nepal (Western Region)

******
[1] Cholera - Nepal (Rautahat District)
Date: Fri 6 Jun 2014
Source: Republica [edited]
http://www.myrepublica.com/portal/index.php?action=news_details&news_id=76514


At least 2 people have died and over 900 affected by cholera since the outbreak of the disease started a month and a half ago in Gaidatar VDC [village development committee] of Rautahat district. The VDC lies 55 km [34 mi] to the north of the district headquarters, Gaur.

The outbreak, which started after the local water source was contaminated with fecal matter, can spread to nearby villages, doctors in the district said.

Duryodhan Prasad Chandrabanshi, acting superintendent at the District Public Health Office (DPHO), Rautahat, said, on Friday alone [6 Jun 2014], over 2 dozen new cholera patients visited the health camp set up in the village and the condition of 3 children among them is critical.

After the number of cholera patients started to rise, 300 bottles of saline and medicine were supplied to the health camp set up on the premises of Janashakti Secondary School.

It is learnt that the source of drinking water in the village became contaminated due to open defecation by the locals of Dhiyal VDC in Makawanpur even after the district was declared open defecation free. Dhiyal VDC is located upstream of the stream that flows past Gaidakot.

[Byline: Madan Thakur]

--
